{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013i59GtmaK11JNRC2mb2uXh","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t#!/usr/bin/env bash\n2\t# Refuses any push targeting refs/heads/main on origin.\n3\t# Override with --no-verify if you really mean it (but you shouldn't).\n4\t\n5\tset -euo pipefail\n6\t\n7\tprotected_branch=\"refs/heads/main\"\n8\t\n9\twhile read -r local_ref local_sha remote_ref remote_sha; do\n10\t    if [ \"$remote_ref\" = \"$protected_branch\" ]; then\n11\t        echo \"\"\n12\t        echo \"ERROR: direct push to main is not allowed.\"\n13\t        echo \"\"\n14\t        echo \"  Local:  $local_ref ($local_sha)\"\n15\t        echo \"  Remote: $remote_ref\"\n16\t        echo \"\"\n17\t        echo \"Open a pull request instead:\"\n18\t        echo \"  1. Create a branch:  git checkout -b <type>/<short-description>\"\n19\t        echo \"  2. Push the branch:  git push -u origin <branch>\"\n20\t        echo \"  3. Open a PR:        gh pr create --base main\"\n21\t        echo \"\"\n22\t        echo \"If you absolutely must push to main, bypass with --no-verify.\"\n23\t        echo \"(But you should not. The point of this hook is to make you stop and think.)\"\n24\t        echo \"\"\n25\t        exit 1\n26\t    fi\n27\tdone\n28\t\n29\texit 0\n30\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b548c412-0178-42a3-bdde-2ff0b36ffc80","uuid":"94b6e098-eb7d-4c3e-a711-82ab6d305cd3","timestamp":"2026-04-08T20:10:46.883Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/sksizer2/Developer/DarkFactory/.worktrees/PRD-230-main-branch-protection/.scripts/git-hooks/pre-push","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Refuses any push targeting refs/heads/main on origin.\n# Override with --no-verify if you really mean it (but you shouldn't).\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nprotected_branch=\"refs/heads/main\"\n\nwhile read -r local_ref local_sha remote_ref remote_sha; do\n    if [ \"$remote_ref\" = \"$protected_branch\" ]; then\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"ERROR: direct push to main is not allowed.\"\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"  Local:  $local_ref ($local_sha)\"\n        echo \"  Remote: $remote_ref\"\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"Open a pull request instead:\"\n        echo \"  1. Create a branch:  git checkout -b <type>/<short-description>\"\n        echo \"  2. Push the branch:  git push -u origin <branch>\"\n        echo \"  3. Open a PR:        gh pr create --base main\"\n        echo \"\"\n        echo \"If you absolutely must push to main, bypass with --no-verify.\"\n        echo \"(But you should not. The point of this hook is to make you stop and think.)\"\n        echo \"\"\n        exit 1\n    fi\ndone\n\nexit 0\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":30}}}
