{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01EMYGUVeEaCK5kpTDAJqRzw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've implemented PRD-230 with two layers of protection against direct pushes to `main`:\n\n**Files created:**\n1. `.scripts/git-hooks/pre-push` — A bash hook that intercepts pushes and refuses any targeting `refs/heads/main` with a clear error message and guidance to use PR workflow\n2. `scripts/install-hooks.sh` — An idempotent installer script that symlinks the hook into `.git/hooks/`\n3. `README.md` — Updated Quick start section to document the install step\n\n**How it works:**\n- The pre-push hook reads git's stdin and checks each push target\n- If `remote_ref == \"refs/heads/main\"`, it exits with error code 1 and prints helpful instructions\n- The installer script symlinks tracked hooks into `.git/hooks/` (which git won't track)\n- The README guides new contributors to run the installer during setup\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n\n- AC-1: PASS — `.scripts/git-hooks/pre-push` exists, is executable, refuses `refs/heads/main` pushes with clear error message and setup guidance\n- AC-2: PASS — `scripts/install-hooks.sh` symlinks hook idempotently, backing up any existing non-symlink hooks\n- AC-3: PASS — Hook reads stdin and checks `remote_ref`, exits code 1 for main with descriptive error\n- AC-4: PASS — Hook only blocks `refs/heads/main`; feature branch pushes pass through with exit 0\n- AC-5: PASS — README updated in Quick start section with `./scripts/install-hooks.sh` instruction\n- AC-6: DEFER — GitHub branch protection must be configured manually in repo Settings → Branches (after PR merge)\n- AC-7: PASS — Hook mechanism prevents direct main pushes locally before network round-trip\n\n**Test status:** All 325 existing tests pass. New code adds no dependencies or complexity.\n\nAll changes are staged and ready for commit.\n\nPRD_EXECUTE_OK: PRD-230"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_